 A farmer named Mufutau Adekola is currently facing trial at a Magistrateâ€™s Court sitting in Ilorin, Kwara State, over the alleged murder of his mother and brother. Adekola was reported to have committed culpable homicide contrary to the provisions of Section 221 of the Penal Code Law. Earlier, the Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Folorunsho Zacheaus, told the court that Adekola attacked his mother, Rafatu; and brother, Mukaila, while they were sleeping on March 9, at Oke-Ode in Ifelodun Local Government Area of the state. The defendant pleaded the court to set him free but Magistrate Ibrahim Dasuki did not take his plea for lack of jurisdiction. The court, on Wednesday, ordered that he should be remanded at the Oke-Kura Correctional Centre pending legal advice on the matter. Dasuki adjourned the case till April 25 for mention. (NAN). 